---js
const layout = "layouts/home.njk";
const title = "Freelance Full-Stack Developer";
const description = "Matt Richards — freelance full-stack developer in Berlin. End-to-end product engineering, TypeScript top to bottom, Node and BFFs. Twenty years in.";
const sitemap = { priority: "0.9", changefreq: "monthly" };
---
{% css %}
@layer page {
	{% include "css/landing.css" %}
	{% include "css/services-grid.css" %}
}
{% endcss %}

<article class="landing">
	<nav class="landing-crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
		<a href="/">Home</a>
		<span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
		<a href="/freelance-tech-lead-berlin/">Freelance</a>
		<span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
		<span aria-current="page">Freelance full-stack developer, Berlin</span>
	</nav>

	<header class="landing-hero">
		<p class="landing-eyebrow">Matt Richards &middot; Berlin</p>
		<h1>Freelance full-stack developer. <em>Berlin.</em></h1>
		<p class="lede">Senior freelance full-stack engineer in Berlin. End-to-end product engineering on the web: DOM to database, Node or BFF, the unglamorous middle where most product value actually lives. TypeScript top to bottom, shipped.</p>
		<div class="landing-meta">
			<a class="eyebrow-link" href="/contact">Start a conversation</a>
			<span class="landing-locator"><span class="online-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Currently open to new work</span>
		</div>
	</header>

	<section class="landing-services" aria-label="What I bring as a freelance full-stack developer">
		<div class="service">
			<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 01</span>
			<h2 class="service-head">Product surface ownership</h2>
			<p class="service-body">One engineer, one vertical, end-to-end. A feature or a product surface I'll own from schema to pixel, with senior judgement at every layer.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="service">
			<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 02</span>
			<h2 class="service-head">TypeScript, top to bottom</h2>
			<p class="service-body">React on the front. Node, tRPC, BFFs and API layers in the middle. One shared type system across the whole stack, held taut.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="service">
			<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 03</span>
			<h2 class="service-head">Data &amp; API design</h2>
			<p class="service-body">Schemas that survive the next three features. APIs that read like product, not like an ORM's stack trace. The boring parts, taken seriously.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="landing-section">
		<h2><span class="ix">&sect; 04 &mdash; What I'm for</span>The engagements that fit</h2>
		<div class="landing-body">
			<p>I work best with product teams small enough that one senior engineer owning a product surface end-to-end actually pays off &mdash; founders, early-stage scale-ups, product orgs running lean. Senior depth across the full web stack, platform-first, without the translation tax.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Embedded full-stack engineer</strong> &mdash; on a product team, shipping features across the whole stack while I'm there.</li>
				<li><strong>Product surface owner</strong> &mdash; a feature, a vertical, a new product. From schema and API to UI and polish.</li>
				<li><strong>Greenfield build</strong> &mdash; a new product or service, from first commit to first customers. Sensible stack choices, boring where boring pays.</li>
				<li><strong>Technical co-founder surrogate</strong> &mdash; short-term, scoped, while you hire. Enough to keep momentum without locking you in.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="landing-section">
		<h2><span class="ix">&sect; 05 &mdash; How I work</span>Fundamentals, first.</h2>
		<div class="landing-body">
			<p>Platform-first. HTML, CSS and the DOM do most of the heavy lifting on the front end. On the back end: clean boundaries, appropriate coupling, schemas and APIs that age well. SOLID where it earns its keep; pragmatism where it doesn't.</p>
			<p>AI is part of how I build now &mdash; used every day, kept on a short leash. Shipping at speed without shipping rot. <a href="/ai-for-engineering-teams-berlin/">More on AI for engineering teams &rarr;</a></p>
			<p>Twenty years across product and platform. I know how to keep humans, products and codebases healthy in times like these. <a href="/about">More about how I work &rarr;</a></p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="services-section" aria-labelledby="related-services-heading">
		<h2 id="related-services-heading">Related services</h2>
		<ul class="services-grid">
			<li class="service">
				<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 01</span>
				<h3 class="service-head">Freelance frontend</h3>
				<p class="service-body">React, TypeScript, modern CSS. Accessible, performant interfaces. Design systems that stay coherent.</p>
				<a class="cta" href="/freelance-frontend-developer-berlin/">Freelance frontend in Berlin</a>
			</li>
			<li class="service">
				<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 02</span>
				<h3 class="service-head">Fractional engineering lead</h3>
				<p class="service-body">Senior engineering leadership, part-time. Strategy, team shape, architecture, mentorship.</p>
				<a class="cta" href="/fractional-engineering-lead-berlin/">Fractional engineering lead</a>
			</li>
			<li class="service">
				<span class="service-kicker">&sect; 03</span>
				<h3 class="service-head">Freelance tech lead</h3>
				<p class="service-body">Hands-on technical leadership. Twenty years in. Berlin, EU, remote.</p>
				<a class="cta" href="/freelance-tech-lead-berlin/">Freelance tech lead, Berlin</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="landing-next" aria-label="Where to go next">
		<div class="next">
			<span class="next-kicker">Background</span>
			<h3>About</h3>
			<p>Twenty years, two sides of the bench: product engineering and engineering leadership.</p>
			<a class="cta" href="/about">Read the long version</a>
		</div>
		<div class="next">
			<span class="next-kicker">Writing</span>
			<h3>Words</h3>
			<p>Notes on craft, leadership, and the age of AI. The archive &mdash; dated, unvarnished.</p>
			<a class="cta" href="/words">Open the archive</a>
		</div>
		<div class="next">
			<span class="next-kicker">Work together</span>
			<h3>Contact</h3>
			<p>Email, Signal, or the form. Tell me what you're building and what's in the way.</p>
			<a class="cta" href="/contact">Get in touch</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</article>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@graph": [
		{
			"@type": "Person",
			"@id": "{{ metadata.url }}/#matt",
			"name": "Matt Richards",
			"alternateName": "tthew",
			"jobTitle": "Freelance Full-Stack Developer",
			"description": "Senior+ freelance full-stack engineer in Berlin. TypeScript top-to-bottom, Node and BFFs, end-to-end product surfaces.",
			"url": "{{ metadata.url }}/",
			"email": "mailto:hallo@tthew.berlin",
			"image": "{{ metadata.url }}/img/1564326180592.jpeg",
			"sameAs": [
				"https://hachyderm.io/@tthew",
				"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tthew/",
				"https://github.com/tthew"
			],
			"address": { "@type": "PostalAddress", "addressLocality": "Berlin", "addressCountry": "DE" },
			"knowsAbout": [
				"Full-stack engineering",
				"TypeScript",
				"Node.js",
				"React",
				"API design",
				"Data modelling",
				"Product engineering"
			]
		},
		{
			"@type": "ProfessionalService",
			"@id": "{{ metadata.url }}{{ page.url }}#service",
			"name": "Matt Richards — Freelance Full-Stack Developer, Berlin",
			"description": "Senior freelance full-stack engineering on the web: end-to-end product surfaces, TypeScript across the stack, Node, BFFs, API and data design. Berlin, EU, remote.",
			"url": "{{ metadata.url }}{{ page.url }}",
			"image": "{{ metadata.url }}/img/1564326180592.jpeg",
			"provider": { "@id": "{{ metadata.url }}/#matt" },
			"areaServed": [
				{ "@type": "City", "name": "Berlin" },
				{ "@type": "Country", "name": "Germany" },
				{ "@type": "Place", "name": "European Union" },
				{ "@type": "Place", "name": "Remote" }
			],
			"serviceType": [
				"Freelance full-stack developer",
				"Freelance full-stack engineer",
				"Freelance TypeScript engineer",
				"Freelance Node.js developer",
				"Freelance software engineer"
			]
		},
		{
			"@type": "BreadcrumbList",
			"itemListElement": [
				{ "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ metadata.url }}/" },
				{ "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Freelance tech lead, Berlin", "item": "{{ metadata.url }}/freelance-tech-lead-berlin/" },
				{ "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Freelance full-stack developer, Berlin", "item": "{{ metadata.url }}{{ page.url }}" }
			]
		}
	]
}
</script>
